def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    if level is None:
        level = group_axis.names
    else:
        level = ensure_categorical(level, group_axis)
        
    if isinstance(key, str):
        key = [key]

    keys = key
    levels = level

    code = obj._codes_for_grouping(group_axis, level, const=True)
    groupings = []
    exclusions = []
    
    for i, (gpr, level) in enumerate(zip(keys, levels)):
        if gpr in obj:
            in_axis = True
            obj._check_label_or_level_ambiguity(gpr)
            # Always regular indexer for grouping along the columns
            ping = Grouping(group_axis, gpr, obj, name=gpr, level=level, sort=sort, observed=observed, in_axis=in_axis, all_groupings=None)                
            groupings.append(ping)
            exclusions.append(gpr)
        else:
            raise KeyError(gpr)

    grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, level=code.levshape, names=code.levels, labels=code.labels)
    return grouper, exclusions, obj
